Afro-rave proponent Rema has explained what informed his decision to acquire a tertiary education. The “Soundgasm” singer, in a post on the microblogging app, revealed he just gained admission into the University of Lagos (UNILAG). The 21-year-old Jonzing World/Mavin artiste did not disclose the course he would be studying.   Hellfire memes fabricated, says son of trending Mummy GO     Maritime varsity didn’t receive N3b from NIMASA, says VC     Trailer kills woman, injures four in Anambra crash   He, however, noted his decision was pre-informed by his mother’s desire for him to acquire a university degree. - Advertisement - “What if I told y’all I got an admission into Unilag? Lol! Mom said I still need to get a degree sigh, oh well see you guys in class!” he wrote. Born Divine Ikubor, he grew up singing and rapping while in secondary school. He attained his primary and secondary school education at Ighile group of schools, Edo State.